00:13:33,500 --> 00:13:36,458
is with my Super-Secret
Ninja Art: The Fun Bag Fondle!

273
00:13:36,541 --> 00:13:38,125
Let go of me this instant!

274
00:13:38,208 --> 00:13:41,333
Kagura,
ignore her lecherous demands.

275
00:13:41,416 --> 00:13:43,666
-Lower the barrier.
-[KAGURA] Uh, okay.

276
00:13:43,750 --> 00:13:46,000
Katsu never changes,
does she?

277
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:48,125
[IKARUGA]
That's the truth.

278
00:13:48,208 --> 00:13:49,833
[KATSURAGI laughing]

279
00:13:49,916 --> 00:13:51,750
[YUMI] I am not above using my
skills as a ninja to stop you!

280
00:13:51,833 --> 00:13:52,833
Katsuragi!

281
00:13:52,916 --> 00:13:54,250
[HOMURA]
Asuka...

282
00:13:54,333 --> 00:13:56,666
what kind of secrets
are you keeping from me?

283
00:13:56,750 --> 00:13:59,750
♪

284
00:14:02,250 --> 00:14:06,708
♪

285
00:14:09,750 --> 00:14:11,125
Come on, everyone,

286
00:14:11,208 --> 00:14:13,375
check out our super special
Christmas discount!

287
00:14:13,458 --> 00:14:14,791
Take one.

288
00:14:14,875 --> 00:14:16,666
Christmas is right around
the corner, you know!

289
00:14:16,750 --> 00:14:20,583
Not buying presents will
land you on the naughty list!

290
00:14:20,666 --> 00:14:21,583
Hey.

291
00:14:21,666 --> 00:14:23,208
What's your deal, Homura?

292
00:14:23,291 --> 00:14:25,666
You haven't said anything
since we've been out here.

293
00:14:25,750 --> 00:14:27,666
Oh, yeah, I'm sorry.

294
00:14:27,750 --> 00:14:29,958
I guess I was just lost
in my thoughts.

295
00:14:30,041 --> 00:14:31,291
Try to cheer up.

296
00:14:31,375 --> 00:14:33,125
You're the one
who wanted a turkey.

297
00:14:33,208 --> 00:14:34,958
And we'll need money for that.

298
00:14:35,041 --> 00:14:37,000
Plus I'll make us dessert, too.

299
00:14:37,083 --> 00:14:40,458
Doesn't a bean sprout cake
sound absolutely scrumptious?

300
00:14:40,541 --> 00:14:41,625
[HOMURA]
Sure.

301
00:14:41,708 --> 00:14:44,208
Hey, look who it is.

302
00:14:44,291 --> 00:14:45,708
[MURASAKI] That doesn't seem
like something

303
00:14:45,791 --> 00:14:47,583
that would be fun
to wear in the cold.

304
00:14:47,666 --> 00:14:49,708
Well, to rogue shinobi
such as ourselves,

305
00:14:49,791 --> 00:14:51,958
a job is a job no matter
what we have to wear.

306
00:14:52,041 --> 00:14:55,041
Except it appears that no one
is actually looking at you.

307
00:14:55,125 --> 00:14:56,791
Huh?

308
00:14:56,875 --> 00:14:57,958
Yeah, she's right.

309
00:14:58,041 --> 00:14:59,625
Ahh!

310
00:14:59,708 --> 00:15:01,250
Man, this blows!

311
00:15:01,333 --> 00:15:03,250
We'll have to do a show
or something to draw attention.

312
00:15:03,333 --> 00:15:06,583
As if! That's not what consumers
wanna see, you sillyhead!

313
00:15:06,666 --> 00:15:09,333
[HOMURA] So what, are you saying
you have a better idea, Ryona?

314
00:15:09,416 --> 00:15:10,541
Uh-huh!

315
00:15:10,625 --> 00:15:13,291
I have a surefire trick
for success!

316
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:16,250
[HOMURA gasps]

317
00:15:16,333 --> 00:15:19,250
[ALL gasp]

318
00:15:19,333 --> 00:15:22,250
Hey! What do you think
you're doing, you pervert?

319
00:15:22,333 --> 00:15:23,458
[RYONA giggles]

320
00:15:23,541 --> 00:15:25,000
-MAN: Yeah, baby!
-[running footsteps]

321
00:15:25,083 --> 00:15:27,000
[men clamoring]

322
00:15:27,083 --> 00:15:29,458
That's quite the increase
in attention.

323
00:15:29,541 --> 00:15:31,041
It actually worked!

324
00:15:33,583 --> 00:15:35,875
Wow, that crowd is crazy.

325
00:15:35,958 --> 00:15:38,625
Suzune-Sensei has gone
to Kikai Dome.

326
00:15:38,708 --> 00:15:41,208
She's requested that you look
after things in her absence.

327
00:15:41,291 --> 00:15:42,541
Understood.

328
00:15:44,791 --> 00:15:45,916
Something wrong?

329
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:47,458
I was thinking
about the technique

330
00:15:47,541 --> 00:15:48,791
that Asuka used.

331
00:15:48,875 --> 00:15:50,000
Oh, yeah.

332
00:15:50,083 --> 00:15:51,791
I've never heard
of that move before.

333
00:15:51,875 --> 00:15:54,333
More importantly, why would
she seal away the youma

334
00:15:54,416 --> 00:15:56,291
instead of just
killing it outright?

335
00:15:56,375 --> 00:15:57,750
No clue.

336
00:15:57,833 --> 00:16:00,375
To be honest, Asuka's been
pretty secretive lately.

337
00:16:00,458 --> 00:16:03,541
She refuses to tell me anything.

338
00:16:03,625 --> 00:16:05,708
I see. Still, though.

339
00:16:05,791 --> 00:16:08,000
I hope she's hasn't chosen
to side with the youma.

340
00:16:08,083 --> 00:16:09,833
I won't forgive her
if she does.

341
00:16:11,375 --> 00:16:13,291
After all, it is
a shinobi's duty

342
00:16:13,375 --> 00:16:15,291
to eliminate threats
like the youma.

343
00:16:15,375 --> 00:16:17,333
♪

344
00:16:26,666 --> 00:16:28,375
-[YUMI] Asuka.
-Huh?

345
00:16:30,833 --> 00:16:31,833
[ASUKA]
Yumi.

346
00:16:33,083 --> 00:16:34,375
Hello there.

347
00:16:34,458 --> 00:16:36,333
I was hoping we could chat.

348
00:16:41,416 --> 00:16:46,375
♪

349
00:16:48,750 --> 00:16:50,291
[ASUKA]
So, what did you need?

350
00:16:52,916 --> 00:16:54,541
Hey, there's no rush.

351
00:16:54,625 --> 00:16:57,916
Let's drink some tea
and warm up a little bit.

352
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,500
[slurping quietly]

353
00:16:59,583 --> 00:17:00,541
Right.

354
00:17:01,916 --> 00:17:03,416
[slurping quietly]

355
00:17:03,500 --> 00:17:04,583
[chuckles]

356
00:17:04,666 --> 00:17:06,291
Delicious.

357
00:17:06,375 --> 00:17:08,291
Have you ever been
to this cafe before?

358
00:17:09,333 --> 00:17:11,000
Yeah, a couple of times.

359
00:17:11,083 --> 00:17:12,791
It's pretty close to home.

360
00:17:12,875 --> 00:17:14,541
So I used to come here often.

361
00:17:15,541 --> 00:17:17,666
Sometimes, Grandpa
would even join me,

362
00:17:17,750 --> 00:17:19,125
and we would eat together.

363
00:17:19,208 --> 00:17:20,958
That sounds wonderful.

364
00:17:22,458 --> 00:17:25,166
I'm glad, you seem more like
your old self lately.

365
00:17:27,250 --> 00:17:28,291
Really?

366
00:17:28,375 --> 00:17:30,166
Then I guess
that's a good thing.

367
00:17:32,958 --> 00:17:34,125
[YUMI]
I think so.

368
00:17:34,208 --> 00:17:36,208
I've been so worried.

369
00:17:36,291 --> 00:17:37,875
What happened to you?

370
00:17:37,958 --> 00:17:39,000
[ASUKA gasps]

371
00:17:39,083 --> 00:17:41,916
[wind whooshing]

372
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:44,916
♪

373
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:49,750
[footsteps approaching]

374
00:17:54,541 --> 00:17:57,583
I've decided
not to kill you, Asuka.

375
00:17:57,666 --> 00:18:00,708
I need you alive
so you can share a message.

376
00:18:00,791 --> 00:18:02,250
The shinobi's dark past.

377
00:18:06,750 --> 00:18:08,000
Which is...

378
00:18:08,083 --> 00:18:10,708
[inaudible dialogue]

379
00:18:10,791 --> 00:18:12,083
[gasps]

380
00:18:15,375 --> 00:18:18,375
There you have it. Those are
the sins of the shinobi.

381
00:18:18,458 --> 00:18:21,250
♪

382
00:18:22,958 --> 00:18:26,708
[ASUKA sobbing softly]

383
00:18:26,791 --> 00:18:29,000
♪

384
00:18:32,083 --> 00:18:33,333
[ASUKA]
I can't tell you.

385
00:18:34,333 --> 00:18:36,041
Why not, Asuka?

386
00:18:42,541 --> 00:18:44,083
I wish you would
at least explain

387
00:18:44,166 --> 00:18:46,041
why you won't talk
about what happened.

388
00:18:51,875 --> 00:18:53,500
Fine, we're not
friends anymore.

389
00:18:53,583 --> 00:18:55,083
[gasps]

390
00:18:55,166 --> 00:18:57,250
♪

391
00:18:57,333 --> 00:18:59,833
A real friend would never be
so secretive.

392
00:18:59,916 --> 00:19:01,833
I guess that means
we're not friends.

393
00:19:01,916 --> 00:19:03,500
That's not fair!

394
00:19:03,583 --> 00:19:06,125
I can tell you're carrying
some sort of burden,

395
00:19:06,208 --> 00:19:07,500
and that's fine.

396
00:19:07,583 --> 00:19:09,708
But Asuka, it shouldn't have
to be something

397
00:19:09,791 --> 00:19:11,500
that you carry
all by yourself.

398
00:19:11,583 --> 00:19:15,416
As a shinobi and your friend,
let me help you.

399
00:19:16,416 --> 00:19:18,083
[ASUKA]
Yumi.

400
00:19:18,166 --> 00:19:19,625
It'll be okay!

401
00:19:19,708 --> 00:19:22,625
No matter what,
we can overcome it together!

402
00:19:22,708 --> 00:19:25,083
♪

403
00:19:27,166 --> 00:19:29,125
All right then.

404
00:19:29,208 --> 00:19:31,458
Guess I'll just be leaving.

405
00:19:31,541 --> 00:19:33,166
You've put me
in a tough spot.

406
00:19:34,166 --> 00:19:35,208
But you win.

407
00:19:35,291 --> 00:19:37,208
I'll tell you, okay.

408
00:19:37,291 --> 00:19:39,416
It's about time!

409
00:19:39,500 --> 00:19:41,250
[FUBUKI] In that case,
perhaps she should hear

410
00:19:41,333 --> 00:19:42,291
everything from me.

411
00:19:42,375 --> 00:19:44,291
[BOTH gasp]

412
00:19:44,375 --> 00:19:47,958
♪

413
00:19:48,041 --> 00:19:49,583
[YUMI]
It's Fubuki!

414
00:19:51,708 --> 00:19:52,750
[FUBUKI]
But first,

415
00:19:52,833 --> 00:19:54,166
I have a question.

416
00:19:55,416 --> 00:19:57,333
Since you are a shinobi,

417
00:19:57,416 --> 00:19:59,041
how do you define justice?

418
00:19:59,125 --> 00:20:02,166
Well, it's a belief
that we have to protect.

419
00:20:02,250 --> 00:20:04,666
[FUBUKI] And what is
that belief, exactly?

420
00:20:04,750 --> 00:20:07,125
To fight against evil
until the very end.

421
00:20:08,291 --> 00:20:10,541
How interesting.

422
00:20:10,625 --> 00:20:11,958
And what is that evil?

423
00:20:13,750 --> 00:20:15,416
Where does that evil lie?

424
00:20:15,500 --> 00:20:16,750
[gasps]

425
00:20:16,833 --> 00:20:19,750
[FUBUKI] Ignorance really is
a sin, you know.

426
00:20:20,958 --> 00:20:22,666
I'm not sure what you mean.

427
00:20:22,750 --> 00:20:25,291
The shinobi hunt down youma
like beasts.

428
00:20:25,375 --> 00:20:28,333
All in the name
of so-called "justice."

429
00:20:28,416 --> 00:20:29,916
Because they're evil.

430
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:32,750
However,
what if I told you

431
00:20:32,833 --> 00:20:34,291
that youma could feel love

432
00:20:34,375 --> 00:20:35,666
the way that humans do?

433
00:20:35,750 --> 00:20:37,333
[YUMI gasps]

434
00:20:37,416 --> 00:20:38,583
[FUBUKI]
Just what would you think

435
00:20:38,666 --> 00:20:40,250
of the shinobi's actions, then?

436
00:20:42,041 --> 00:20:44,416
[YUMI] To be honest,
I don't really know.

437
00:20:44,500 --> 00:20:47,250
I was told
the youma were all evil,

438
00:20:47,333 --> 00:20:49,375
so they must be defeated.

439
00:20:49,458 --> 00:20:50,875
Therefore, it's hard to believe

440
00:20:50,958 --> 00:20:53,500
that the justice
of the shinobi is wrong.

441
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:55,875
Still though,

442
00:20:55,958 --> 00:20:58,708
if what you've just told me
is really the truth,

443
00:20:58,791 --> 00:21:01,458
then I, I think
that it's unforgivable.

444
00:21:05,208 --> 00:21:07,083
[FUBUKI]
Very well, I will show you.

445
00:21:07,166 --> 00:21:08,000
[gasps]

446
00:21:09,333 --> 00:21:11,333
I have proof
the youma feel love.

447
00:21:12,333 --> 00:21:13,666
Just like you.

448
00:21:15,041 --> 00:21:16,208
[YUMI/ASUKA gasp]

449
00:21:16,291 --> 00:21:18,000
Wait, her aura.

450
00:21:18,083 --> 00:21:19,750
It's like a youma's!

451
00:21:19,833 --> 00:21:21,083
How can that be?

452
00:21:21,166 --> 00:21:23,250
[FUBUKI]
Haven't you figured it out?

453
00:21:23,333 --> 00:21:25,416
The answer's rather simple.

454
00:21:25,500 --> 00:21:29,250
It's because I am a child born
from a youma and a human.

455
00:21:29,333 --> 00:21:31,041
[gasps]

456
00:21:35,541 --> 00:21:36,833
I feel it.

457
00:21:36,916 --> 00:21:39,541
A door to the other world
is starting to open.

458
00:21:39,625 --> 00:21:40,708
Really?

459
00:21:40,791 --> 00:21:43,125
It's larger
than the previous one.

460
00:21:43,208 --> 00:21:44,375
If it finishes opening,

461
00:21:44,458 --> 00:21:47,083
something terrible
is going to happen!

462
00:21:47,166 --> 00:21:48,625
Where's the door?

463
00:21:48,708 --> 00:21:50,208
Um, let's see.

464
00:21:50,291 --> 00:21:52,083
[grunting]

465
00:21:55,541 --> 00:21:57,250
It's in the hot springs town!

466
00:21:59,041 --> 00:22:00,208
Seriously?

467
00:22:01,416 --> 00:22:02,541
[KAGURA]
Yes.

468
00:23:33,916 --> 00:23:36,291
Hah! The battle
is just beginning!

469
00:23:36,375 --> 00:23:38,250
Huh! Bring it on, then!

470
00:23:38,333 --> 00:23:39,958
So this is it.

471
00:23:40,041 --> 00:23:41,375
The final battle.

472
00:23:42,708 --> 00:23:45,666
Let's have as much fun as we can
until we fight the youma!

473
00:23:45,750 --> 00:23:48,166
For sure! It'll be
a hot springs party!

